<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-17T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/15240a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-17T20:00:00-04:00">January 17,
                                1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>85. I. In response to a New Year’s greeting sent by the Secretary of the
                            Navy,<note n="24" xml:id="d258fn24">Frank Knox.</note> the Navy
                        Department has received, presumably from the Naval Attaché,<note n="25" xml:id="d258fn25">Capt. Henry T. Jarrell, U. S. Navy.</note> a message
                        reading substantially as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>The Secretary’s message has given Dr. T. V. Soong much gratification.
                                Dr. Soong is pleased to state that Generalissimo is coming to
                                realize that Soong’s differences of opinion are based on China’s
                                welfare and that the tension between Soong and the Generalissimo is
                                greatly relaxed.</p>
                        </quote>
                    </p>
                    <p>II. We would be interested in your comments.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>